The paper deals with wireless networks and their performance, which falls under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT). It also considers topological factors such as distances and inter-cell interference, which are related to Networked Systems (cs.NI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also proposes novel signal management schemes, which could fall under Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Multimedia (cs.MM) depending on the specific application.
